body:
Sorry for bringing up the issue again. I think the top-level-reduction-only restriction still exists in TVM today.

I noticed that `relay.transform.transform.FuseOps` fuses a `conv2d` and a following `relu` into one single function. If I understand correctly, this means, in the underlying TOPI implementation, there will be a `relu` operation outside the reduction from `conv2d` (scheduled via `inline`, `compute_at` or something like that). Such as:

```
for (...) {
  for (...) {
    x += ... // conv2d
  }
  x = relu(x) // relu
}
```

So the reduction loop is no longer at top level any more.

Is the aforementioned fusion really meaningful? Or is the fusion only used for third-party backends such as cuDNN?
